Hundreds of farmers brought Madrid'straffic to a standstill with their tractors in the latestprotest to demand a better deal from the European Community(EC) and more government subsidies to face up to ECcompetition.    Farmers said they had planned to bring their cows with thembut police had prevented their entry into the capital.    In the south, striking shipyard workers clashed with policein the port of Cadiz in what has become a regular weeklyprotest against job layoffs at the state-owned AstillerosEspanoles. The workers locked themselves in the factory andtraded stones for tear gas, police said. Reuter&#3;